2. **Report runtime efficiency benchmarks**: Add training time, inference time, and FLOPs comparisons to substantiate the "CheapNet" naming claim beyond memory savings.

3. **Analyze learned cluster semantics**: Report statistics on cluster composition (e.g., percentage of aromatic atoms, hydrogen bond donors/acceptors, hydrophobic groups per cluster) to show whether biologically relevant groupings emerge.

